text: Villeneuve-sur-Aisne is a commune in the Aisne department in the Hauts-de- France region in northern France. It was created on 1 January 2019. It is made of the former communes of Guignicourt and Menneville.Arrêté préfectoral == Related pages == * Communes of the Aisne department == References == == Other websites == * INSEE commune file Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Aisne
